um border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"273\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC273\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\">  </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <tr class=\"border-0\">\n          <td id=\"L274\" class=\"blob-num border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"274\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC274\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\"> <span class=\"pl-k\">if</span> (<span class=\"pl-smi\">${CAFFE2_CMAKE_USE_LOCAL_FINDCUDA}</span>) </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <tr class=\"border-0\">\n          <td id=\"L275\" class=\"blob-num border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"275\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC275\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\">   <span class=\"pl-c1\">list</span>(<span class=\"pl-k\">APPEND</span> <span class=\"pl-k\">CMAKE_MODULE_PATH</span> <span class=\"pl-smi\">${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}</span>/cmake/Modules_CUDA_fix) </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <tr class=\"border-0\">\n          <td id=\"L276\" class=\"blob-num border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"276\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC276\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\">   <span class=\"pl-c1\">include</span>(CMakeInitializeConfigs) </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <tr class=\"border-0\">\n          <td id=\"L277\" class=\"blob-num border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"277\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC277\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\"> <span class=\"pl-k\">endif</span>() </td>\n        </tr>\n    </tbody></table>\n  </div>\n</div>\n</p>", "body_text": "thanks @soumith ! basically the problem is we include the CUDA fix only in certain versions:\n\n  \n    \n      pytorch/cmake/MiscCheck.cmake\n    \n    \n        Lines 264 to 277\n      in\n      4bf0202\n    \n    \n    \n    \n\n        \n          \n           # ---[ Check if we will need to include the local Modules_CUDA_fix folder. \n        \n\n        \n          \n           # Add your conditions here if needed. \n        \n\n        \n          \n           if (MSVC) \n        \n\n        \n          \n             # We know that VS2017 needs the new FindCUDA functionality, so we will \n        \n\n        \n          \n             # simply enable it for the whole Windows build. \n        \n\n        \n          \n             set(CAFFE2_CMAKE_USE_LOCAL_FINDCUDA ON) \n        \n\n        \n          \n           else (${CMAKE_VERSION} VERSION_LESS 3.12 AND ${USE_CUDA}) \n        \n\n        \n          \n             set(CAFFE2_CMAKE_USE_LOCAL_FINDCUDA ON) \n        \n\n        \n          \n           endif() \n        \n\n        \n          \n            \n        \n\n        \n          \n           if (${CAFFE2_CMAKE_USE_LOCAL_FINDCUDA}) \n        \n\n        \n          \n             list(APPEND CMAKE_MODULE_PATH ${PROJECT_SOURCE_DIR}/cmake/Modules_CUDA_fix) \n        \n\n        \n          \n             include(CMakeInitializeConfigs) \n        \n\n        \n          \n           endif()", "body": "thanks @soumith ! basically the problem is we include the CUDA fix only in certain versions:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/4bf0202cac4cdf95bf437df5d2e8a8c5bb892569/cmake/MiscCheck.cmake#L264-L277"}